Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

In a #bowl{} coat the @British chicken thighs{4} with half the @mayonnaise{2}, stir to combine. Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25} on a #plate{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place the chicken in the breadcrumbs one at a time and coat on both sides with the crumbs - press the chicken down on the crumbs to ensure you get an even coating. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Trim the @carrot{2}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the carrot. Stop when you get to the core. Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Put the carrot and spring onion in a bowl and set aside. In another #small bowl{} stir the remaining mayonnaise and @sriracha sauce{1} together.

Heat a glug of @oil{a glug} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. When hot, add the chicken and fry on both sides until golden and crunchy ~{3-4%minutes} per side - be careful when you turn the chicken not to knock the crumbs off. Once golden, remove the pan from the heat and lay the chicken thighs on a baking tray, pop them in the oven and bake for ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @honey{15}, @ginger puree{1} and a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} to the carrot and spring onion. Use your hands to ensure that it is evenly coated. Season to taste with @salt{}.

Half the @burger buns{2} and warm them in the oven for ~{2%minutes}. Spoon the sriracha mayonnaise (be careful it's spicy!) onto the base of each bun and top with 2 chicken thighs per person. Pop the bun lid on, share the slaw between your plates and serve with the wedges alongside. Enjoy!